features.feature: 亲爱的用户，本次更新图库新增反光消除、表情修复、闭眼修复、水印编辑功能，支持动态照片拼图、编辑功能，优化录屏、截屏、任意门、锁屏、智慧多窗和骚扰拦截等功能使用体验，推荐您进行更新。
• 新增动态照片拼图功能。体验路径：图库 > 选中多张动态照片 > 创作 > 拼图。 • 新增动态照片编辑功能。体验路径：图库 > 查看动态照片 > AI 编辑。
• 新增图片反光消除功能。体验路径：图库 > 查看图片 > AI 编辑 > 魔法修图 > AI 消除 > 反光消除。
• 新增照片表情修复功能。体验路径：图库 > 查看人像照片 > AI 编辑 > 魔法修图 > 人脸修复 > 表情修复。
• 新增闭眼修复功能。体验路径：图库 > 选择照片 > AI 编辑 > 魔法修图 > 人脸修复 > 闭眼修复。
• 优化图片水印编辑功能，可对部分水印元素进行添加或编辑。体验路径：图库 > 查看图片 > AI 编辑 > 水印。
• 新增录屏暂停功能。体验路径：启动录屏 > 录屏悬浮窗 > 点击录屏暂停按钮。 • 新增录屏隐藏通知消息弹框功能。体验路径：设置 > 辅助功能 > 屏幕录制 > 录屏隐藏通知。
• 新增截屏分享后删除原图功能。体验路径：截屏 > 分享 > 勾选分享后删除截图。
• 优化任意门图片拖拽功能。支持部分应用界面内可拖拽单张完整的长图，长图不再截断。
• 铃声选择界面 UX 焕新，提升用户使用体验。

• 新增锁屏界面左下角手电筒快速开启入口，可向上拖动开启手电筒功能。 • 新增锁屏密码触感反馈功能，在锁屏数字密码输入界面输入时伴随振动效果，提升输入体验。 • 新增“我的锁屏”栏，展示锁屏历史记录，支持设置或者删除。体验路径：设置 > 桌面和个性化 > 锁屏样式 > 自定义 > 锁屏样式 > 我的锁屏。 • 优化双击熄屏功能，双击锁屏空白处也可快速熄屏。体验路径：设置 > 辅助功能 > 快捷启动及手势 > 亮屏/熄屏 > 双击熄屏。 • 优化锁屏底部按钮交互，支持自定义设置。体验路径：设置 > 桌面和个性化 > 锁屏样式 > 自定义 > 点击左/右下角图标。
• 新增控制中心滑动音量条/亮度条到最大或最小时的振动效果。
• 新增悬浮窗风格选项，选择简洁风格可将悬浮窗顶部按钮隐藏至顶部小横条中。体验路径：设置 > 辅助功能 > 智慧多窗 > 悬浮窗风格。
• 优化蓝牙耳机电量显示，在蓝牙设置页面及控制中心展开蓝牙详情页面支持显示蓝牙耳机电量。体验路径：设置 > 蓝牙 > 已配对的设备。
• 新增支持与 iPhone 互传文件。在苹果 App Store 中下载“荣耀互联”应用即可体验高速免流量互传。
• 新增指南针振动反馈效果，当手机转动到正方向 (如：正南方向) 时，伴随振动效果，提升指南针使用体验。
• 新增返回手势振动效果，增强返回手势振动体验。体验路径：设置 > 声音和振动 > 返回手势反馈。 • 优化系统触感反馈设置层级，将系统触感反馈开关由“设置 > 声音和振动 > 更多声音和振动设置”三级页面提拉到“声音和振动”二级页面下，方便用户快捷开关。
• 新增支持 WLAN 密码输入可粘贴功能，提升输入效率。
• 新增个人热点界面支持截屏，分享热点更便捷。
• 新增应用剪贴板权限控制开关，可通过此开关管理应用读取剪贴板内容的权限。体验路径：设置 > 应用 > 应用管理 > 选择应用 > 权限 > 剪贴板。
• 新增隐藏应用功能，支持隐藏应用的桌面图标、桌面搜索入口、消息通知、最近任务等能力。体验路径：设置 > 隐私 > 隐藏应用。
• 新增支持拦截虚拟运营商电话功能，为您提供更好的骚扰拦截体验。体验路径：系统管家 > 骚扰拦截 > 拦截规则 > 电话拦截规则。 • 新增按地区号码拦截来电功能。体验路径：系统管家 > 骚扰拦截 > 拦截规则 > 拦截国际地区陌生号码和拦截归属地陌生号码。
• 合入安卓 2025 年 6 月安全补丁，增强系统安全性。有关荣耀软件安全更新内容的信息，请访问荣耀官方网站 https://www.honor.com/cn/support/bulletin/2025/6
1. 本次更新不会删除您的用户数据，但仍建议您在更新前做好数据备份。 2. 更多精彩功能介绍，请访问“玩机技巧”应用。 3. 如果您在使用过程中遇到任何问题，请访问“我的荣耀”应用或访问荣耀官方服务网站 https://www.honor.com/cn/contact-us 寻求支持。

Dear user, this update enhances Gallery with Remove reflection, Expression Fix, Eyes Open and Edit watermarks features. You can now edit moving photos and create moving photo collages. This update also optimizes the user experience of screen recording, screenshot, Magic Portal, Multi-Window, lock screen and Blocked features. Update to enjoy the new features and improvements.

• You can create moving photo collages. Try it out by going to: Gallery > Select multiple moving photos > Create > Collage. • You can also edit moving photos. Try it out by going to: Gallery > View a moving photo > AI Edit.
• AI Edit includes Remove reflection feature. Try it out by going to: Gallery > View an image > AI Edit > Magic Retouch > AI Eraser > Remove reflection.
• Expression Fix is now available in Gallery. Try it out by going to: Gallery > View a portrait photo > AI Edit > Magic Retouch > Face Tune > Expression Fix.
• Eyes Open can now be used for image editing. Try it out by going to: Gallery > Select an image > AI Edit > Magic Retouch > Face Tune > Eyes Open.
• AI Edit allows you to add or edit specific watermark elements. Try it out by going to: Gallery > View an image > AI Edit > Watermark.

• You can now pause screen recording. Start screen recording, then go to the floating window and tap the pause button. • You can also hide notification pop-ups during screen recording. Try it out by going to: Settings > Accessibility features > Screen recording > Hide notifications while screen recording.
• The screenshot can be automatically deleted after it has been shared. Take a screenshot first, then tap Share, and check the Delete screenshot after sharing option.
• Optimizes the image drag-and-drop feature in Magic Portal. Certain apps allow you to drag and drop a complete long image without any truncation.
• The design of Phone ringtone interface has been refreshed to enhance the user experience.

• Quick access to Flashlight is available in the bottom left corner of the lock screen. You can drag it upwards to turn Flashlight on. • Lock screen password input includes haptic feedback. When you enter password on the lock screen, it vibrates to enhance the typing experience. • My lockscreens column shows your lock screen history. You can set any of them as your current lock screen or delete them. Try it out by going to: Settings > Home screen & style > Lock screen style > Custom > Lock screen style > My lockscreens. • You can now quickly turn off the screen by double-tapping an empty space of the lock screen. Try it out by going to: Settings > Accessibility features > Shortcuts & gestures > Screen On/Off > Double tap to turn off screen. • The widgets at the bottom of the lock screen allow for custom settings. Try it out by going to: Settings > Home screen & style > Lock screen style > Custom > Tap the icon in the lower left/right corner.
• You can feel haptic feedback when you adjust the volume or brightness slider in the Control Center to its maximum or minimum level.

• The Concise style of floating window can hide the control buttons in the small control bar at the top. Try it out by going to: Settings > Accessibility features > Multi-window > Floating window style.

• Optimizes the battery level display of Bluetooth earphones. To check the battery level, you can go to the Bluetooth settings page or go to the Control Center and expand the Bluetooth details. Try it out by going to: Settings > Bluetooth > PAIRED DEVICES.
• It supports file transfer with iPhone. Download Honor Connect from the Apple App Store to experience high-speed and data-free transfers.
• Compass’s vibration feedback enhances the user experience. When you turn the phone to face a cardinal direction, like due south, it vibrates.

• Back gesture haptics feature enables a better tactile experience. Try it out by going to: Settings > Sounds & vibration > Back gesture haptics. • The System haptics toggle is moved from the third-level menu (Settings > Sounds & vibration > More sound settings) to the second-level Sounds & vibration page. This change makes it easier for you to enable or disable the feature.
• Entering Wi-Fi passwords through copy and paste can enhance input efficiency.
• Personal hotspot interface now allows screenshots, making network sharing more convenient.
• You can determine which apps have access to the Clipboard content via Clipboard permission switch. Try it out by going to: Settings > Apps > Manage apps > Select an app > Permissions > Clipboard.

Hidden apps feature allows you to hide selected apps. Home screen icons, notifications, and recent tasks of these apps will not be displayed. Additionally, these hidden apps will not appear in Home screen search. Try it out by going to: Settings > Privacy > Hidden apps.

• Block calls from virtual carriers feature enhances your experience by more effectively blocking spam calls. Try it out by going to: System Manager > Blocked > Block rules > Call block rules. • Block rules now include the ability to block calls based on area codes. Try it out by going to: System Manager > Blocked > Block rules > Block unknown numbers from foreign countries/Block unknown numbers from home location.

• Android security patch (Jun 2025) has been incorporated for system security. For more information about Honor Security updates, please visit our website https://www.honor.com/global/support/bulletin/2025/6

1. Installing this update will not affect your personal data, but it is still recommended to back up your data before updating. 2. Check out more information on product features in the Tips app. 3. If you encounter any problem during use, please get support by going to My Honor or visiting our website: https://www.honor.com/cn/contact-us.
